### Minimum first-run variable:
### - POSTGRES_PASSWORD
###
### Recommended first-run variables for application setup:
### - APP_DB_USER
### - APP_DB_PASSWORD
### - APP_DB_NAME
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=''

### Optional superuser name. Defaults to `postgres`.
POSTGRES_USER='postgres'

### Optional database created on first startup. Defaults to POSTGRES_USER.
POSTGRES_DB='postgres'

### Optional application role + database created on first startup.
### If all three are set, the init script will:
### - CREATE ROLE <APP_DB_USER> LOGIN PASSWORD <APP_DB_PASSWORD>
### - CREATE DATABASE <APP_DB_NAME> OWNER <APP_DB_USER>
### - Grant full privileges on that database/schema to the app role
APP_DB_USER=''
APP_DB_PASSWORD=''
APP_DB_NAME=''

### Optional: absolute path or command name for psql client used by _psql_connect.
### If blank, the script will use `psql` from PATH.
POSTGRES_CLIENT=''

### PostgreSQL listen_addresses. Defaults to '*' (all interfaces).
###
### Network access notes:
### - If you want to connect from containers on the same linux machine,
###   include the docker bridge interface (often 172.17.0.1)
### - If you want external network access, include a network-reachable host interface
### - Client source IP controls are handled by configdir/pg_hba.conf
POSTGRES_LISTEN_ADDRESSES='*'

### Optional host/port defaults for _psql_connect
POSTGRES_HOST='localhost'
POSTGRES_PORT='5432'
